    "label": "Course Aims",
    "value": "To encourage the acquisition of analytical, scientific and communication skills to investigate cyber security incidents  and present appropriate evidence to a non-technical audience, e.g. court-room."
  },
  "intended_learning_outcomes_of_course": {
    "label": "Intended Learning Outcomes of Course",
    "value": "By the end of this course students will be able to:\ncritically evaluate cyber system tools and approaches for a given context;\nunderstand the nature of countermeasures against forensic analysis;\npredict potential ethical, legal and regulatory concerns from gathered forensic evidence;\neffectively communicate complex outcomes from a forensic investigation to a non-technical audience, e.g. court-room."
  },
